cerentMsDwdmMIB.name: cerentMsDwdmMIB

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB.

cerentMsDwdmMIB.contactinfo: support@Cisco.com Postal: Cisco Systems 1450 N. McDowell Blvd. Petaluma, CA 94954 Tel: +1-877-323-7368
cerentMsDwdmMIB.description: This MIB module defines the managed objects for physical layer related interface configurations and objects for the protocol specific error counters for DWDM optical switches. This MIB contains four groups. The first group, cerentMsDwdmIfGroup, handles the physical layer related interface configurations. The second group, cerentMsDwdmOtnGroup, provides objects for configuring OTN (G.709) related thresholds and for collecting OTN (G.709) related performance statistics for the current and previous 15 min and 24 hour intervals. The third group, cerentMsDwdmFECGroup provides objects for monitoring FEC (Fault Error Correction) statistics for the current and previous 15 min and 24 hour intervals. It also contains objects for configuring FEC error thresholds. The fourth group,cerentMsDwdm8B10BGroup contains 8B10B counters, for the current and previous 15 min and 24 hour intervals for interfaces like Fiber Channel/Gig E.

ProtocolType.name: ProtocolType
ProtocolType.description: An integer value that identifies the protocol used across an interface.

IntervalType.name: IntervalType
IntervalType.description: This value indicates the time period over which performance monitoring data has been collected. Valid values are - fifteenMin (1) : values for the 15 min interval. oneDay (2) : values for the 1 Day interval.

LocationAndIntervalType.name: LocationAndIntervalType
LocationAndIntervalType.description: This value indicates the time period and the location for which the performace monitoring data has been collected. Valid values are - nearEnd15Min (1) : nearEnd values for the 15 min interval. nearEndOneDay (2) : nearEnd values for the 1 Day interval. farEnd15Min (3) : farEnd values for the 15 min interval. farEndOneDay (4) : farEnd values for the 1 day interval.

MonitorType.name: MonitorType
MonitorType.description: This value indicates the type of performance statistics being monitored. Valid values are - path(1) : Performance statistics for path parameters. section(2) : Performance statistics for section parameters. tcm1(3) : Performance statistics for tandem connection monitoring 1. tcm2(4) : Performance statistics for tandem connection monitoring 2.

RingDirection.name: RingDirection
RingDirection.description: This value indicates the type of directionality in the ring. The directionality is meaning the facing side of the port that is connected to fiber. Valid values are - westEast(1) : the port is facing to west side, continuing to east side eastWest(2) : the port is facing to east side, continuing to west side

SideIdentifier.name: SideIdentifier
SideIdentifier.description: This value indicates the side in the ring/mesh node e.g. the facing side associated to on optical interface within an up to 8 deg mesh node. Valid values are - unknownSide(0) sideA(1) sideB(2) sideC(3) sideD(4) sideE(5) sideF(6) sideG(7) sideH(8) sideI(9) sideJ(10) sideK(11) sideL(12) sideM(13) sideN(14) sideO(15) sideP(16) sideQ(17) sideR(18) sideS(19) sideT(20)

OpticalPortRule.name: OpticalPortRule
OpticalPortRule.description: This value indicates the rule that assumes the optical port. Valid values are - inputLine(1) : this is an input LINE port outputLine(2) : this is an output LINE port inputCom(3) : this is an input COM port outputCom(4) : this is an output COM port inputOsc(5) : this is an input OSC port outputOsc(6) : this is an output OSC port inputDc(7) : this is an input DCU port outputDc(8) : this is an output DCU port inputExpress(9) : this is an input EXPress port outputExpress(10) : this is an output EXPress port add(11) : this is an band/wavelength ADD port drop(12) : this is an band/wavelength DROP port inputPassThru(13) : this is an input Pass Thru port inputWorking(14) : the working port that receive the signal in an optical protection unit outputWorking(15) : the working port that send the signal in an optical protection unit inputProtected(16) : the protected port that receive the signal in an optical protection unit outputProtected(17) : the protected port that send the signal in an optical protection unit inputRaman(18) : this is an input RAMAN port outputRaman(19) : this is an output RAMAN port com(20) : this is an COM port ead(21) : this is an Express/Add/Drop port ad(22) : this is an Add/Drop port

LaserStatus.name: LaserStatus
LaserStatus.description: This value indicates the working status of the laser. Valid values are - on(1) : laser is working off(2) : laser is switched off apr(3) : laser is working in automatic power reduction none(4) : laser is not present

OpticalAmplifierMode.name: OpticalAmplifierMode
OpticalAmplifierMode.description: This value indicates the amplifier working mode Valid values are - gain(1) : gain control mode power(2) : power control mode none(3) : not an amplifier port fixed-gain(4) : fixed gain control mode

OpticalBand.name: OpticalBand
OpticalBand.description: This value indicates the the wavelength group (band) The following wave lengths group are supported: bn1530d33To1532d68 : are the wavelengths from 1530.33 nm to 1532.68 nm. bn1534d25To1536d61 : are the wavelengths from 1534.25 nm to 1536.61 nm. bn1538d19To1540d56 : are the wavelengths from 1538.19 nm to 1540.56 nm. bn1542d14To1544d53 : are the wavelengths from 1542.14 nm to 1544.53 nm. bn1546d12To1548d51 : are the wavelengths from 1546.12 nm to 1548.51 nm. bn1550d12To1552d52 : are the wavelengths from 1550.12 nm to 1552.52 nm. bn1554d13To1556d55 : are the wavelengths from 1554.13 nm to 1556.55 nm. bn1558d17To1560d61 : are the wavelengths from 1558.17 nm to 1560.61 nm.

OpticalPowerInDbm.name: OpticalPowerInDbm
OpticalPowerInDbm.description: An integer value that gives the optical power level in 1/10ths of dBm. Example: The value -300 represents a power level of -30.0 dBm. The distinguished value of '-1000' indicates that the object has not yet been initialized.

OpticalAttenInDb.name: OpticalAttenInDb
OpticalAttenInDb.description: An integer value that gives the attenuation level in 1/10ths of dB. Example: The value 80 represents an attenuation level of 8.0 dB.

TDCUCompensation.name: TDCUCompensation
TDCUCompensation.description: Enumeration of the possible fine TDCU compensation values 0 ps/nm -45 ps/nm -90 ps/nm -135 ps/nm -180 ps/nm -225 ps/nm -270 ps/nm -315 ps/nm -360 ps/nm -405 ps/nm -450 ps/nm -495 ps/nm -540 ps/nm -585 ps/nm -630 ps/nm -675 ps/nm Enumeration of the possible coarse TDCU compensation values 0 ps/nm -110 ps/nm -220 ps/nm -330 ps/nm -440 ps/nm -550 ps/nm -660 ps/nm -770 ps/nm -880 ps/nm -990 ps/nm -1100 ps/nm -1210 ps/nm -1320 ps/nm -1430 ps/nm -1540 ps/nm -1650 ps/nm

cMsDwdmIfConfigTable.name: cMsDwdmIfConfigTable
cMsDwdmIfConfigTable.description: This table allows physical layer related interface configurations on an interface.

cMsDwdmIfConfigEntry.name: cMsDwdmIfConfigEntry
cMsDwdmIfConfigEntry.description: A collection of objects for configuration on an interface.

cMsDwdmIfConfigProtocol.name: cMsDwdmIfConfigProtocol
cMsDwdmIfConfigProtocol.description: This object is used to specify the protocol of the data carried over the interface. This object applies to linecards which support a variety of protocols and allow dynamic configuration of the specific protocol to be monitored on the interface. The ifType value for such interfaces remains fixed.

cMsDwdmIfConfigDataRate.name: cMsDwdmIfConfigDataRate
cMsDwdmIfConfigDataRate.description: This object allows the management client to set the data rate across the interface. passThru denotes 2R, Reamplification and reshaping. stm1 denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. stm4 denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. stm16 denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. stm64 denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. gigE denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. tenGigE denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. fc denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. oneGfcFicon denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. twoGfcFiconIsc3 denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. escon denotes 2R, Reamp and reshaping. dv6000 denotes 2R, Reamp and reshaping. sdiD1Video denotes 2R, Reamp and reshaping. hdtv denotes 2R, Reamp and reshaping. oc3 denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. oc12 denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. oc48 denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. oc192 denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. infiniBand denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. fe denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. e3t3 denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking. oc3Ge denotes 3R, Reamp, reshaping and reclocking.

cMsDwdmIfConfigLoopback.name: cMsDwdmIfConfigLoopback
cMsDwdmIfConfigLoopback.description: This object allows the management client to configure loopback for the client side or trunk side interfaces. 'noLoop' - No Loopback present. 'diagnosticLoop' - This is an internal loopback, where the data stream is looped from the transmit to receive section. It is used for hardware debug, bring-up and diagnostics. 'lineLoop' - In this mode, the receive data stream is looped back to the transmit side. 'otherLoop' - This indicates loopbacks not defined here. The default value of this object will be 'noLoop'.

cMsDwdmIfConfigWavelength.name: cMsDwdmIfConfigWavelength
cMsDwdmIfConfigWavelength.description: This object allows the management client to configure the wavelength mode of operation to the applicable interfaces.

cMsDwdmIfConfigOtnStatus.name: cMsDwdmIfConfigOtnStatus
cMsDwdmIfConfigOtnStatus.description: This object allows the management client to enable the OTN (G.709) on an applicable interface,by writing a value of 'true' to this object. To bypass the monitoring hardware, a value of 'false' is written to this object. This object is not applicable to client side interfaces.

cMsDwdmIfConfigFECStatus.name: cMsDwdmIfConfigFECStatus
cMsDwdmIfConfigFECStatus.description: This object allows the management client to enable gathering FEC ( Forward Error Correction ) counters on an applicable interface, by writing a value of 'true' to this object.To disable FEC, a value of 'false' must be written to this object. This object is not applicable to client side interfaces. This object is being replaced by cMsDwdmIfConfigFECMode and is going to become obsolete in the future releases.

cMsDwdmIfOpticsValidIntervals.name: cMsDwdmIfOpticsValidIntervals
cMsDwdmIfOpticsValidIntervals.description: This object gives the number of contiguous 15 minute intervals for which valid Optical Monitor PM data is available for the particular interface. The value of this object will be n (where n is the maximum number of 15 minute intervals supported at this interface), unless the measurement was (re-)started within the last (nx15) minutes, in which case the value will be the number of 15 minute intervals for which the agent has some data.

cMsDwdmIfOTNValidIntervals.name: cMsDwdmIfOTNValidIntervals
cMsDwdmIfOTNValidIntervals.description: This object gives the number of contiguous 15 minute intervals for which valid OTN performance monitoring data is available for the particular interface. The value of this object will be n (where n is the maximum number of 15 minute intervals supported at this interface), unless the measurement was (re-)started within the last (nx15) minutes, in which case the value will be the number of 15 minute intervals for which the agent has some data. This object reports a value 0, if OTN is turned off.

cMsDwdmIfFECValidIntervals.name: cMsDwdmIfFECValidIntervals
cMsDwdmIfFECValidIntervals.description: This object gives the number of contiguous 15 minute intervals for which valid FEC PM data is available for the particular interface. The value of this object will be n (where n is the maximum number of 15 minute intervals supported at this interface), unless the measurement was (re-)started within the last (nx15) minutes, in which case the value will be the number of 15 minute intervals for which the agent has some data. This object reports a value 0, if FEC is turned off.

cMsDwdmIfConfigFECMode.name: cMsDwdmIfConfigFECMode
cMsDwdmIfConfigFECMode.description: This object allows the management client to enable gathering FEC ( Forward Error Correction ) counters on an applicable interface, by writing a value of 'enableStandard' or 'enableEnhanced' to this object. To disable FEC, a value of 'disable' must be written to this object. This object is not applicable to client side interfaces.

cMsDwdmIfTransportTable.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportTable
cMsDwdmIfTransportTable.description: This table defines optical transport layer related interface configurations on an interface.

cMsDwdmIfTransportEntry.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportEntry
cMsDwdmIfTransportEntry.description: A collection of objects for configuration on an optical transport interface.

cMsDwdmIfTransportRingDirection.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportRingDirection
cMsDwdmIfTransportRingDirection.description: This object is used to specify the ring directionality of the port. The ring directionality gives the configuration of the facing side: facing sides can be east going to west and west going to east.

cMsDwdmIfTransportPortRule.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportPortRule
cMsDwdmIfTransportPortRule.description: This object is used to specify the type of the optical port. A transport optical port can assume one of the following values: input(1) input-express(2) output(3) output-express(4).

cMsDwdmIfTransportPower.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportPower
cMsDwdmIfTransportPower.description: This object is used to specify the optical power read at the photodiode of the port. The distinguished value of '-1000' indicates that the power cannot be read due to unavaible HW resource.

cMsDwdmIfTransportReferencePower.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportReferencePower
cMsDwdmIfTransportReferencePower.description: This object is used to specify the optical transport reference power. This is the value of power the network element will expect on the photodiode. In case the user wants to refine this value the 'cMsDwdmIfTransportCalibratedPower' can be used to add an offset to the network element setup value.

cMsDwdmIfTransportCalibratedPower.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportCalibratedPower
cMsDwdmIfTransportCalibratedPower.description: This object is used to specify the optical transport calibration power. This is the power offset that user contribute in case the 'reference' value setup by network element would be modified.

cMsDwdmIfTransportInsertionLoss.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportInsertionLoss
cMsDwdmIfTransportInsertionLoss.description: This object is used to specify the value of Insertion Loss of the optical port.

cMsDwdmIfTransportLaserStatus.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportLaserStatus
cMsDwdmIfTransportLaserStatus.description: This object is used to specify the status of the laser.

cMsDwdmIfTransportAmplifierMode.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportAmplifierMode
cMsDwdmIfTransportAmplifierMode.description: This object is used to specify the working amplifier mode.

cMsDwdmIfTransportGain.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportGain
cMsDwdmIfTransportGain.description: This object is used to specify the value of the gain of an amplifier

cMsDwdmIfTransportReferenceTilt.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportReferenceTilt
cMsDwdmIfTransportReferenceTilt.description: This object is used to specify the amplifier tilt value calculated by the network element.

cMsDwdmIfTransportCalibratedTilt.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportCalibratedTilt
cMsDwdmIfTransportCalibratedTilt.description: This object is used to specify the amplifier tilt offset added as offset by user in order to tune the network element calculated ('reference') value

cMsDwdmIfTransportDCULoss.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportDCULoss
cMsDwdmIfTransportDCULoss.description: This object is used to specify the value of Insertion Loss measured for the Dispersion Compensation Unit

cMsDwdmIfTransportOSRI.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportOSRI
cMsDwdmIfTransportOSRI.description: This value indicates the status of the Optical Safety Remote Interlock Valid values are - enable(1) : the OSRI is enable disable(2) : the OSRI is disable none(3) : the OSRI functionality is not present

cMsDwdmIfTransportExpectedGain.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportExpectedGain
cMsDwdmIfTransportExpectedGain.description: This object is used to specify the value of the expected gain of an amplifier

cMsDwdmIfTransportSideIdentifier.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportSideIdentifier
cMsDwdmIfTransportSideIdentifier.description: This object is used to specify the facing side of the optical port.

cMsDwdmIfTransportTDCUCompensation.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportTDCUCompensation
cMsDwdmIfTransportTDCUCompensation.description: This object is used to specify the TDCU Compensation value of the optical port belong to a TDCU card.

cMsDwdmIfTransportAddPower.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportAddPower
cMsDwdmIfTransportAddPower.description: This object is used to specify the ADD optical power read at the photodiode of the port. The distinguished value of '-1000' indicates that the power cannot be read due to unavaible HW resource.

cMsDwdmIfTransportOSCPower.name: cMsDwdmIfTransportOSCPower
cMsDwdmIfTransportOSCPower.description: This object is used to specify the OSC optical power read at the photodiode of the port. The distinguished value of '-1000' indicates that the power cannot be read due to unavaible HW resource.

cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionTable.name: cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionTable
cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionTable.description: This table defines optical multiplex section (band) layer related interface configurations on an interface.

cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionEntry.name: cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionEntry
cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionEntry.description: A collection of objects for configuration on an optical multiplex section (band) interface.

cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionRingDirection.name: cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionRingDirection
cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionRingDirection.description: This object is used to specify the ring directionality of the port. The ring directionality gives the configuration of the facing side: facing sides can be east going to west and west going to east.

cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionPortRule.name: cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionPortRule
cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionPortRule.description: This object is used to specify the type of the optical port. A Multiplex Section optical port can assume one of the following values: add(5) drop(6).

cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionPower.name: cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionPower
cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionPower.description: This object is used to specify the optical power read at the photodiode of the port. The distinguished value of '-1000' indicates that the power cannot be read due to unavaible HW resource.

cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionReferencePower.name: cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionReferencePower

This is the value of power the network element will expect on the photodiode. In case the user wants to refine this value the 'cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionCalibratedPower' can be used to add an offset to the network element setup value.

cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionInsertionLoss.name: cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionInsertionLoss

cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionActualBand.name: cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionActualBand
cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionActualBand.description: This object is used to specify the value of Wavelength group which is tuned the optical port.

cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionExpectedBand.name: cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionExpectedBand
cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionExpectedBand.description: This object is used to specify the value of Wavelength group that the user expects the optical port will assume.

cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionSideIdentifier.name: cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionSideIdentifier
cMsDwdmIfMultiplexSectionSideIdentifier.description: This object is used to specify the facing side of the optical port.

cMsDwdmIfChannelTable.name: cMsDwdmIfChannelTable
cMsDwdmIfChannelTable.description: This table defines optical channel layer related interface configurations on an interface.

cMsDwdmIfChannelEntry.name: cMsDwdmIfChannelEntry
cMsDwdmIfChannelEntry.description: A collection of objects for configuration on an optical channel interface.

cMsDwdmIfChannelRingDirection.name: cMsDwdmIfChannelRingDirection
cMsDwdmIfChannelRingDirection.description: This object is used to specify the ring directionality of the port. The ring directionality gives the configuration of the facing side: facing sides can be east going to west and west going to east.

cMsDwdmIfChannelPortRule.name: cMsDwdmIfChannelPortRule
cMsDwdmIfChannelPortRule.description: This object is used to specify the type of the optical port. A Multiplex Section optical port can assume one of the following values: add(5) drop(6).

cMsDwdmIfChannelPower.name: cMsDwdmIfChannelPower
cMsDwdmIfChannelPower.description: This object is used to specify the optical power read at the photodiode of the port. The distinguished value of '-1000' indicates that the power cannot be read due to unavaible HW resource.

cMsDwdmIfChannelReferencePower.name: cMsDwdmIfChannelReferencePower
cMsDwdmIfChannelReferencePower.description: This object is used to specify the optical Multiplex Section reference power. This is the value of power the network element will expect on the photodiode. In case the user wants to refine this value the 'cMsDwdmIfChannelCalibratedPower' can be used to add an offset to the network element setup value.

cMsDwdmIfChannelCalibratedPower.name: cMsDwdmIfChannelCalibratedPower
cMsDwdmIfChannelCalibratedPower.description: This object is used to specify the optical Channel calibration power. This is the power offset that user contribute in case the 'reference' value setup by network element would be modified.

cMsDwdmIfChannelInsertionLoss.name: cMsDwdmIfChannelInsertionLoss
cMsDwdmIfChannelInsertionLoss.description: This object is used to specify the value of Insertion Loss of the optical port.

cMsDwdmIfChannelActualWavelength.name: cMsDwdmIfChannelActualWavelength
cMsDwdmIfChannelActualWavelength.description: This object is used to specify the value of Wavelength that is tuned the optical port.

cMsDwdmIfChannelExpectedWavelength.name: cMsDwdmIfChannelExpectedWavelength

cMsDwdmIfChannelSideIdentifier.name: cMsDwdmIfChannelSideIdentifier
cMsDwdmIfChannelSideIdentifier.description: This object is used to specify the facing side of the optical port.

cMsDwdmOtnThresholdsTable.name: cMsDwdmOtnThresholdsTable
cMsDwdmOtnThresholdsTable.description: This table provides objects for configuring OTN ( G.709 ) thresholds on trunk side interfaces.

cMsDwdmOtnThreshMonType.name: cMsDwdmOtnThreshMonType
cMsDwdmOtnThreshMonType.description: This object is an index to the cMsDwdmOtnThresholdsTable. It is used to specify the type of monitoring threshold being set on an interface for OTN ( G.709 ) statistics.

cMsDwdmOtnThreshIntervalType.name: cMsDwdmOtnThreshIntervalType
cMsDwdmOtnThreshIntervalType.description: This object is an index to the cMsDwdmOtnThresholdsTable. It specifies the interval type and monitoring location for the performance statistics.

cMsDwdmOtnThreshFC.name: cMsDwdmOtnThreshFC
cMsDwdmOtnThreshFC.description: This object is used to set the threshold for the number of failure counts on applicable trunk side interfaces.

cMsDwdmOtnThreshES.name: cMsDwdmOtnThreshES
cMsDwdmOtnThreshES.description: This object is used to set the threshold for the number of Errored Seconds on applicable trunk side interfaces.

cMsDwdmOtnThreshSES.name: cMsDwdmOtnThreshSES
cMsDwdmOtnThreshSES.description: This object is used to set the threshold for the number of Severely Errored Seconds on applicable trunk side interfaces.

cMsDwdmOtnThreshUAS.name: cMsDwdmOtnThreshUAS
cMsDwdmOtnThreshUAS.description: This object is used to set the threshold for the number of Unavailable Seconds on applicable trunk side interfaces.

cMsDwdmOtnThreshBBE.name: cMsDwdmOtnThreshBBE
cMsDwdmOtnThreshBBE.description: This object is used to set the threshold for the number of Bit Block Errors on applicable trunk side interfaces.

cMsDwdmOtnCurrentTable.name: cMsDwdmOtnCurrentTable
cMsDwdmOtnCurrentTable.description: This table contains the cumulative OTN (G.709) PM stats for the trunk side interfaces.

cMsDwdmOtnCurrentMonType.name: cMsDwdmOtnCurrentMonType
cMsDwdmOtnCurrentMonType.description: This object is an index to the cMsDwdmOtnCurrentTable. It is used to otain G.709 statistics for path, section and tcm ( tandem connection).

cMsDwdmOtnCurIntervalType.name: cMsDwdmOtnCurIntervalType
cMsDwdmOtnCurIntervalType.description: This object is an index to the cMsDwdmOtnCurrentTable. It specifies the interval type (farEnd/ nearEnd and 15 min/ 1 Day )for the table objects.

cMsDwdmOtnCurrentFC.name: cMsDwdmOtnCurrentFC
cMsDwdmOtnCurrentFC.description: The counter associated with the number of failure counts encountered on this interface in the current interval.

cMsDwdmOtnCurrentES.name: cMsDwdmOtnCurrentES
cMsDwdmOtnCurrentES.description: The counter associated with the number of Errored Seconds encountered on this interface in the current interval.

cMsDwdmOtnCurrentSES.name: cMsDwdmOtnCurrentSES
cMsDwdmOtnCurrentSES.description: The counter associated with the number of Severely Errored Seconds encountered on this interface in the current interval.

cMsDwdmOtnCurrentUAS.name: cMsDwdmOtnCurrentUAS
cMsDwdmOtnCurrentUAS.description: The counter associated with the number of Unavailable Seconds encountered on this interface in the current interval.

cMsDwdmOtnCurrentBBE.name: cMsDwdmOtnCurrentBBE
cMsDwdmOtnCurrentBBE.description: The counter associated with the number of Background Block Errors encountered on this interface in the current interval.

cMsDwdmOtnCurrentESR.name: cMsDwdmOtnCurrentESR
cMsDwdmOtnCurrentESR.description: The counter associated with the Errored Seconds Ratio on this interface in the current interval.

cMsDwdmOtnCurrentSESR.name: cMsDwdmOtnCurrentSESR
cMsDwdmOtnCurrentSESR.description: The counter associated with the Severely Errored Seconds ratio on this interface in the current interval.

cMsDwdmOtnCurrentBBER.name: cMsDwdmOtnCurrentBBER
cMsDwdmOtnCurrentBBER.description: The counter associated with the Background Block Errors ratio on this interface in the current interval.

cMsDwdmOtnIntervalTable.name: cMsDwdmOtnIntervalTable
cMsDwdmOtnIntervalTable.description: This table contains the cumulative OTN (G.709) PM stats for the trunk side interfaces.

cMsDwdmOtnIntervalMonType.name: cMsDwdmOtnIntervalMonType
cMsDwdmOtnIntervalMonType.description: This object is an index to the cMsDwdmOtnIntervalTable. It is used to otain G.709 statistics for path, section and tcm ( tandem connection).

cMsDwdmOtnIntervalType.name: cMsDwdmOtnIntervalType
cMsDwdmOtnIntervalType.description: This object is an index to the cMsDwdmOtnIntervalTable. It specifies the interval type (farEnd/ nearEnd and 15 min/ 1 Day )for the table objects.

cMsDwdmOtnIntervalNum.name: cMsDwdmOtnIntervalNum
cMsDwdmOtnIntervalNum.description: This object is an index to the cMsDwdmOtnIntervalTable. This object gives the number of the interval. It is a number between 1 and 96, which identifies the interval for which the set of OTN performance values is available. The interval identified by 1 is the most recent 15 minute or 24 hour interval, and the interval identified by N is the interval immediately preceding the one identified by N-1.

cMsDwdmOtnIntervalFC.name: cMsDwdmOtnIntervalFC
cMsDwdmOtnIntervalFC.description: The counter associated with the number of failure counts encountered on this interface in a particular interval.

cMsDwdmOtnIntervalES.name: cMsDwdmOtnIntervalES
cMsDwdmOtnIntervalES.description: The counter associated with the number of Errored Seconds encountered on this interface in a particular interval.

cMsDwdmOtnIntervalSES.name: cMsDwdmOtnIntervalSES
cMsDwdmOtnIntervalSES.description: The counter associated with the number of Severely Errored Seconds encountered on this interface in a particular interval.
